The paper deals with geometric objects such as convex sets, halfspaces, and segments in the plane, and their combinatorial properties such as shattering and VC-dimension. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses range-query data structures, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial aspects, which could place it under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses hypergraphs and their properties, which could place it under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
